cs.NI, cs.SI, cs.DS, cs.SY, cs.CR 

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper discusses the impact of cooperation policy and network topology on in-network caching performance. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is also likely as the paper discusses the relation between content popularity and topological properties. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is relevant as the paper models the cooperation policy with two parameters. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is relevant as the paper discusses the design of in-network caching strategies. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is less likely but still possible as the paper may touch upon security implications of in-network caching.
